  "_doc": "Calibrated session capacity for POINTS-BUDGETED batches (docs/agent/backlog-workflow.md -> 'Running a batch'). The batch's point budget = round(capacityPoints * targetFraction). 'points' = batchCost (a story's size; a task = 2). `node scripts/backlog.mjs calibrate --points=<P> --context-pct=<C>` folds a session into capacityPoints as a CONTEXT-WEIGHTED MEAN over the last 12 samples: each session's implied capacity (points / context-fraction) is weighted by its contextPct, so a high-context session counts far more than an early low-context stop (whose extrapolation is near-noise and biased low by fixed startup overhead). Unlike the previous fixed-alpha EMA this converges as samples accumulate and actually uses the stored history, while the 12-sample window keeps it adaptive to a regime change (e.g. a new model).",
